      <head>Max Marschalk</head>
      <div>
        <p>German composer and music critic. </p>

        <p>Marschalk studied at the Berlin Hochschule für Musik, and became a singing teacher. From
          1894 to 1933, he was the musical critic for the <ref cRef="vossische_zeitung">Vossische
            Zeitung</ref>, and a friend of Gustav Mahler and Richard Strauss. In addition, he was
          director of the music publishing house Dreililien Verlag, the direction of which was
          handed over to Richard Birnbach in 1934. </p>

        <p>There is no known correspondence between Marschalk and Schenker.</p>

      </div>
